<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10078b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10078b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10078b"> 78(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> libel</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les tablettes se restreignirent &agrave; un usage plus personnel. Les lettres proprement dites se multipli&egrave;rent. Les Romains les pliaient en pages, lorsqu&apos;elles avaient quelque &eacute;tendue; ils leur donnaient la forme de petits livres <mark>(libelli)</mark>, les enveloppaient ordinairement de papier &eacute;pais ou de parchemin, ou de d&eacute;bris de vieux livres; les liaient avec un fil et scellaient de leur sceau le noeud de cire ou de mastic. <font color="green">[The tablets were limited to a more personal use. The letters themselves multiplied. The Romans folded them into pages when as they became too long. They gave them the shape of small books (libelli) and typically covered them in thick paper or parchment or with the remains of old books. They bound them with string and sealed them with a knot of wax or mastic.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 47-8</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
